<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[342,561,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Leucospidae" genus="Leucospis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifera">
<emphasis box="[342,561,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Leucospis signifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[908,1013,189,213]" country="Paraguay" name="Asuncion" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<collectingCountry box="[908,1013,189,213]" name="Paraguay" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1136,188,213]" name="Argentina" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1190,1258,188,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(states of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[301,419,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
). This is its first record from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[877,1030,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, which represents the northern most record of this species (
<figureCitation box="[404,491,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,526,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[151,1436,526,1869]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 25. Geographic records of Leucospis in Brazil, based on literature." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1298019/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[503,535,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1665,1687]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,195,1636]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[177,1411,195,1636]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 26. New geographic records of Leucospis in Brazil A. Detail of the state of Minas Gerais. B. New records in Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1298021/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">26</figureCitation>
). Although the identification key differentiates 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1198,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Leucospidae" genus="Leucospis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifera">
<emphasis box="[1068,1198,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">L. signifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1253,1406,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Leucospidae" genus="Leucospis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis box="[1253,1406,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">L. opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is worth noting that only the females of the last species have tergite VI with a spiniform projection on the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
